::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 802211002: Config/Level/Mission/8022110/Act/Act802211002.json-->
::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* Mr. Soda's extra story... What am I gonna do about that one...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} The ''Mr. Soda'' extra story's commercial has aired.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215113-->
::'''Soda Animator:''' Pfft... What!? That was fast!
::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* I feel like a bottle of SoulGlad that someone left the cap off... all out of fizz, with no more ideas bubbling up.
::'''Soda Animator:''' The Mr. Soda character is a co-production between SoulGlad Enterprise and Clock Studios. They say the model for the prototype was based on the drink's creator, Mr. Sousa.
::'''Soda Animator:''' Based on SoulGlad's ads, he was this incredible cook who believed deeply in Harmony. He was kind, selfless, affable, courteous...
::'''Soda Animator:''' But Mr. Watchmaker didn't seem very happy with that version. His character Mr. Soda is nothing like the graceful saint of legend but instead is this buffoon bottle always acting the fool.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is this some kind of prank from the Watchmaker?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215119-->
:::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* Maybe. That chairman has always been at odds with The Family. I bet he won't like a great hero packaged up by the Harmony faith.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is that called artistic license?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215121-->
:::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* Maybe. A self-righteous saint harping on about Harmony is boring, so a loveable buffoon like Mr. Soda is going to appeal more widely.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Perhaps that's his real self.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215123-->
:::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* I heard the characters in Clockie are all Mr. Watchmaker's old friends... Maybe the Mr. Sousa known to the chairman was just one such person.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_802215124-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215124-->
::'''Soda Animator:''' No matter how I look at it, I can't integrate the magnificent Mr. Sousa with the rubberface antics of Mr. Soda... Director, you know the Watchmaker, so can you please help me put together this part of the script?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} No problem!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215126-->
:::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* Thank you, this extra story finally has some legs!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Do it yourself.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215128-->
:::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* Don't be like that. I really can't think of anything. Don't make me leave it blank!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Am I doing more unpaid overtime?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215130-->
:::'''Soda Animator:''' *gurgle* Don't be like that. You'll definitely learn plenty of Directorial Skills from this!
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_802215131-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215131-->
::'''Soda Animator:''' Come on, let's get creative in here...
::'''Soda Animator:''' "Ladies and gents, Mr. Soda's story starts before Clockie arrived. Back then, Dreamville was still known as 'Nightmareville,' and Boss Stone ruled the townsfolk with an iron fist. Here we find Mr. Soda, who was a local..."
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Chef.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_802215134-->
:::'''Soda Animator:''' Oh! That's great, and historically accurate too.
